title: King's Command Foods, LLC. Recalls Beef Products Due To Possible Foreign Matter Contamination
summary: EDITORS NOTE: This release is being reissued as an expansion of the March 9, 2017 recall to include additional products and production dates. Details of this release were also updated to reflect a change in poundage. WASHINGTON, March 17, 2017 Kings Command Foods, LLC., a...
impacted_products: 28-lb. case bulk packages of “FULLY COOKED MEATBALLS” bearing case code 72355 with packaging dates of 5-16-16, 5-24-16, 8-11-16 and 10-05-16.
10-lb. case bulk packages of “FULLY COOKED Certified Angus Beef Brand MEATBALLS” bearing case code 72090.
